        "content": "<p>This result doesn't seem to be in mathlib, and would be a good lemma for <code>minpoly.lean</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">lemma</span> <span class=\"n\">my_lemma</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">A</span> <span class=\"n\">B</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">comm_ring</span> <span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">ring</span> <span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">algebra</span> <span class=\"n\">A</span> <span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">b</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"o\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hb</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">minpoly</span> <span class=\"n\">A</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">degree</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span> <span class=\"bp\">âˆˆ</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">algebra_map</span> <span class=\"n\">A</span> <span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">range</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>There seem to be several ways to prove this, but I can't seem to find the necessary sublemmas in mathlib.</p>\n<p>For instance, does mathlib know that a polynomial of degree 1 has a unique root?</p>",
